    "body": "### Problem\n\n![Image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/3481c64e-42c9-49a6-8216-707103dfb427)\n\nIn my plugin, I need to draw a block of highlight area, to give visual note of my last block selection, but normal extmark are not able to do that, I had to use virt_text with hl group and fill it by empty characters as work-around.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nA new optional parameter of nvim_buf_set_extmark, allow extmark to bind with absolute position like ' marks did (to not move with buffer changes), and support virtual highlighting (set hl group on void), give extmark more freedom.",
